        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:56PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Cripple Creek, or 28 miles west of Colorado Springs,
moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, penny size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Fremont and southwestern Teller Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
